---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const lastUpdated = "February 5, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="Terms of use for PrivacyFix. Free privacy tools and educational content provided as-is."
>
  <article class="py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <header class="mb-12">
          <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Terms of Use</h1>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)]">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        </header>

        <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
          <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 mb-8">
            <p class="text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium mb-2">
              Important Notice
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)]">
              PrivacyFix provides free educational content and tools. We are not lawyers and this is not legal advice.
              For specific legal questions, consult a qualified attorney.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            By accessing and using PrivacyFix ("the Site"), you accept and agree to be bound by these Terms of Use.
            If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the Site.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">2. Description of Service</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            PrivacyFix provides:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <li>Free privacy assessment tools and calculators</li>
            <li>Educational guides about data privacy rights</li>
            <li>Information about data broker opt-out processes</li>
            <li>Links to third-party privacy services (some may be affiliate links)</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">3. No Legal Advice</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <strong>The content on this Site is for informational and educational purposes only.</strong>
            It does not constitute legal advice and should not be relied upon as such.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            Privacy laws vary by jurisdiction and change frequently. The information we provide may not be
            current, complete, or applicable to your specific situation. Always consult with a qualified
            attorney for legal advice specific to your circumstances.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">4. No Professional Advice</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            Our tools and guides are provided for general informational purposes. They are not a substitute for
            professional advice from attorneys, privacy consultants, or other qualified professionals.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">5. Accuracy of Information</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            We strive to provide accurate and up-to-date information, but we make no warranties or representations
            about the accuracy, completeness, or reliability of any content on the Site.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            Privacy laws, data broker practices, and opt-out processes change frequently. Information that was
            accurate when published may become outdated. Always verify current requirements before taking action.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">6. Use of Tools</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            Our privacy tools (Privacy Audit, Opt-Out Tracker, etc.) are provided free of charge for personal,
            non-commercial use. By using these tools, you understand that:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <li>All calculations and assessments are performed locally in your browser</li>
            <li>Results are estimates based on the information you provide</li>
            <li>We are not responsible for actions you take based on tool outputs</li>
            <li>Tool functionality may change or be discontinued at any time</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">7. Third-Party Links and Services</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            The Site contains links to third-party websites and services, including data removal services,
            VPN providers, and identity protection services. Some of these are affiliate links.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            We are not responsible for the content, accuracy, or practices of third-party sites.
            Your use of third-party services is governed by their terms and privacy policies.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <strong>To the fullest extent permitted by law, PrivacyFix and its operators shall not be liable
            for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <li>Your use of or inability to use the Site</li>
            <li>Any errors or omissions in the content</li>
            <li>Actions you take based on information from the Site</li>
            <li>Unauthorized access to or alteration of your data</li>
            <li>Any third-party conduct or content</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <strong>Our maximum liability is limited to $0 (zero dollars)</strong>, as the service is provided
            free of charge.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">9. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            The Site and all content are provided "AS IS" and "AS AVAILABLE" without warranties of any kind,
            either express or implied, including but not limited to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <li>Implied warranties of merchantability</li>
            <li>Fitness for a particular purpose</li>
            <li>Non-infringement</li>
            <li>Accuracy, reliability, or completeness of content</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">10. Indemnification</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            You agree to indemnify and hold harmless PrivacyFix and its operators from any claims, damages,
            losses, or expenses arising from your use of the Site or violation of these Terms.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">11. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. Changes will be posted on this page
            with an updated date. Continued use of the Site after changes constitutes acceptance of the
            modified Terms.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">12. Governing Law</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            These Terms are governed by applicable laws. Any disputes will be resolved in accordance with
            those laws.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">13. Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            Questions about these Terms? Email us at
            <a href="mailto:legal@getprivacyfix.com" class="text-emerald-500 hover:text-emerald-600">legal@getprivacyfix.com</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
